        <div class="col-md-6">
            <p>
                A clinic management system (CMS) is a software solution designed to streamline and automate the administrative and operational tasks of a medical clinic or healthcare facility. 
                It helps healthcare providers manage patient information, appointments, billing, and other aspects of their practice.
            </p>
            <p>
                Clinic management systems are crucial for improving overall efficiency, reducing paperwork, minimizing errors, and enhancing the overall quality of patient care in healthcare settings. Numerous commercial and open-source solutions are available to meet the diverse needs of healthcare providers. 
                When selecting a clinic management system, it's important to consider factors such as scalability, user-friendliness, and compatibility with existing workflows.
            </p>
